**Changes:**
- Attempts to fetch the alternate IP address (public if we used private, vice versa)
- Shows both variants with proper labels (`public` or `private`)
- Includes `sudo` in the kubectl command
- Uses explicit `--kubeconfig /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf` path
- Changed command to `get po -A -o wide` (all namespaces, all pods, wide format)
- Falls back to placeholders (`<public-ip>` or `<private-ip>`) if the alternate IP can't be fetched
